{
  "version": "1.0",
  "metadata": {
    "title": "Heavy Current",
    "bpm": 138,
    "timeSignature": [
      4,
      4
    ],
    "key": "A minor",
    "description": "Bass-forward trance mix with a drum & bass break in the middle. 138 BPM, A minor, 16 bars across four 4-bar sections: intro → trance → dnb-break → return. The reese bass is the star — off-beat trance pattern in the trance sections, rolling 8th-note pattern in the break. No supersaw lead — the 'primarily bassy' brief means the bass carries the melodic movement. Kick→pad sidechain gives the trance sections their pumping feel; the DnB break pulls the sub bass out and lets the reese bass carry the low end alone over DnB-style kick/snare (kick on 1 and 2&, snare on 2 and 4). Chord progression: Am–F–C–G (i–VI–III–VII).",
    "tags": [
      "trance",
      "drum-and-bass",
      "bass-driven",
      "reese-bass",
      "sidechained",
      "hybrid"
    ]
  },
